data.title: Serving the University Community Since 1958
data.text:
Open Houses at Princeton University’s Eating Clubs

Princeton Prospect Foundation provides for periodic public access to Princeton University’s iconic eating clubs where generations of students have taken meals and socialized in historic and architecturally significant clubhouses that date as far back as 1895. There is no fee to visit the clubs during open houses, nor are reservations required. The next open houses will be held from 1:30 p.m. to 4:30 p.m. on successive Sundays in the fall semester of 2024, grouped as follows:

November 10th: Cannon Club, Cap & Gown Club, Colonial Club, Ivy Club, Terrace Club, Tower Club

November 17th: Charter Club, Cloister Inn, Cottage Club, Quadrangle Club, Tiger Inn
